    {
      "id": 2,
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Jupiter vs fallback — both sides",
      "description": "The #116/0.2.1 soak instrument. Left axis: curve serves the price-service actually answered (all zones, per hour). Right axis (0/1 steps): zeus's verdict per cycle — zeus_price_source code 0 = healthy jupiter/primary serve, code 1 = zeus fell through to its DIRECT ENTSO-E fallback (price-service unreachable). With prices.source=jupiter (live since #108), sustained code 0 + a steady serve rate = sustained jupiter-sourced cycles; a flip to code 1 while serves drop = zeus riding the fallback. Codes 2/3/4 (cache/none/partial) are on the PRICE_SOURCE timeline below.",
